cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CC, cs.CR

This paper deals with reasoning in a logic that unifies several nonmonotonic formalisms, including default logic, autoepistemic logic, circumscription, epistemic queries, and logic programming. This makes it relevant to several areas of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), logic (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), computational complexity (cs.CC), and cryptography (cs.CR). However, since the paper focuses on the complexity and algorithms for reasoning in the logic, cs.CC and cs.PL are less likely than cs.AI and cs.LO. Additionally, the paper does not deal with cryptography directly, so cs.CR is the least likely category.
